Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Munaf Patel, out Bowled!! You don't need to be a genius at this. Anyone can see that Munaf Patel has no chance against the swinging and pacy Bhuvneshwar. Especially at the death. Munaf Patel doesn't get in line, just stands outside leg and wafts his bat through the line. The late reverse swing takes the leg stump out and sends it out of its groove. That's clinical execution at the death. Perhaps the best exponent with the ball when bowling at the end in the world. Munaf Patel b Bhuvneshwar 0(1)

Commentary Text: Siraj to Sangwan, out Bowled!! Two in two. Before this ball, Siraj was talking to Bhuvi as he set the field. Whatever he spoke, he executed to perfection. Inswinger, lands on a length and goes through the bat and pad gap of Sangwan. Too big a gap and the ball finds its way through to the stumps. Siraj ends with a four-fer. What a story he has been this IPL. The whole of Old City in Hyderabad will be tucking into their biriyanis watching this. Certainly made his folks proud. Sangwan b Siraj 0(1)

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Karthik, out Caught by Deepak Hooda!! Wow. Wow. Three wickets in quick time and suddenly the score isn't looking that great. High full toss, was meant to be hit for six but Karthik mistimed that and looked like it was falling in front of the fielder, but Hooda came in and snaffled that low and diving forward. Rashid Khan can't contain his smile. Can't believe his luck either. DK just puts his head down in disappointment, unable to believe the shot he played. Karthik c Deepak Hooda b Rashid Khan 0(1)

Commentary Text: Siraj to Raina, out Caught by Dhawan!! What a wicket that is. Two in the over for Siraj. A game-changing over? Will only know once the match is done. But certainly SRH now get a chance to come back into the game. Wasn't a great delivery, off-pace and down leg, but Raina found Dhawan at deep backward square. After taking the catch, he puts a finger to his lip and points to the crowd suggesting to keep quiet. Typical Dhawan. Raina c Dhawan b Siraj 2(5)

Commentary Text: P Kumar to Dhawan, out Caught by Faulkner!! A nothing shot from Dhawan and the Sunrisers have been jolted early. Change in pace has done Dhawan in completely, he was setting himself up for the pull as Praveen pitched it short - the change of pace meant that the ball didn't come onto the bat at all, he was through with the shot and only manages to toe-end it towards mid-on. Faulkner runs forward, puts in the slide and holds on. Dhawan c Faulkner b P Kumar 18(11) [4s-4]
